{"id":37203,"title":"[Intravitreal implantation of Ozurdex® chronic delivery system for management of macular edema related to retinitis pigmentosa: case report].","abstract":"Retinitis pigmentosa denotes a heterogeneous group of rare genetic diseases in which both rods and cones eye are damaged. It is a disease of poor prognosis. We describe the case of a 22 years old woman successfully treated with intravitreal implant of dexamentasone (OZURDEX®, Allergan, USA) for the treatment of macular edema due to retinitis pigmentosa.","date":"2014-02-10","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24510088","annotations":[{"name":"Genetic disorder","weight":0.851115,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetic_disorder"},{"name":"Edema","weight":0.802901,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edema"},{"name":"Chronic (medicine)","weight":0.79352,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronic_(medicine)"},{"name":"Prognosis","weight":0.752214,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prognosis"},{"name":"Genetics","weight":0.735174,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetics"},{"name":"Human eye","weight":0.725566,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_eye"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Cutaneous conditions","weight":0.546948,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cutaneous_conditions"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.359539,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Macular edema","weight":0.341701,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macular_edema"},{"name":"Homogeneity and heterogeneity","weight":0.307222,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homogeneity_and_heterogeneity"},{"name":"United States","weight":0.225165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_State